1/4 cup oil

  1 red bell pepper, coarsely diced
  2 medium potatoes, peeled and coarsely diced
  2 large carrots, peeled and cubed
  1 small onion, peeled and chopped
  3 cloves garlic, peeled and minced
  1 thumb ginger, peeled and minced
  4 lbs chicken, diced

  1 Tbsp fish sauce
  2 cups coconut milk
  1 cup water
  2 Tbsp curry powder
1/2 cup cashews


In wide pan over medium heat, heat oil.
Add chicken; cook until browned
Add onions, garlic, ginger; cook until soft
Add 1 Tbsp fish sauce; cook 1 minute
Add 2 cups coconut milk and 1 cup water; bring to simmer
Lower heat, add potatoes, cover and simmer 20 to 30 minutes
Add carrots; cook 3 to 5 minutes
Add 2 Tbsp curry powder, stir to combine; cook 2 to 3 minutes
Season with salt and pepper to taste
Add bell peppers and cashews and cook 1 minute
Serve over rice
